c WMC regression for DVE weight folding via a GATE definition (not plain equiv).
c x2 is definable by x1 through clauses -1 2 / 1 -2, while x1 itself is pinned
c by a gate (3 4 / -3 -5 / 2 5), so the definability is exercised on a different
c structural path than t30's bare equivalence. x2 again has an ASYMMETRIC weight
c whose two sides collide at 15 significant figures but differ in exact value
c (1/3 vs 100000000000000000003/300000000000000000000).
c Guards the same two bugs as t30, but reached through a gate:
c  - candidate selection must use exact equals(), not to_string();
c  - an eliminated definable var's weight must be folded into weight_factor.
c Sci answer (all vars projected): 1.04166666666667e-01.
c t wmc
c p weight 1 1/2 0
c p weight -1 1/2 0
c p weight 2 1/3 0
c p weight -2 100000000000000000003/300000000000000000000 0
c p weight 3 1/2 0
c p weight -3 1/2 0
c p weight 4 1/2 0
c p weight -4 1/2 0
c p weight 5 1/2 0
c p weight -5 1/2 0
p cnf 5 5
3 4 0
-1 2 0
1 -2 0
2 5 0
-3 -5 0
